p: Forty-five percent of the strains exhibited MIC values for oxytetracycline of less than 100 μg mL -1 ( Table 5). Forty-five percent of the strains presented MIC values between 200–500 μg mL -1 ( Table 5). Ten percent of the strains presented a high MIC value for oxytetracycline (> 3500 μg mL -1, Table 5). All strains presented sensitivity to florfenicol at low concentrations (≤ 40 μg mL -1, Table 5).
